---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import LessonNav from '../../components/LessonNav.astro';
import LessonAudio from '../../components/LessonAudio.astro';
---
<Layout title="Lesson 2: General Requirements">
  <div class="lesson-header">
    <span class="lesson-badge">Lesson 2</span>
    <h1>General Requirements</h1>
    <p class="lesson-subtitle">What every Engineering Portfolio needs before anything else.</p>
    <LessonAudio slug="lesson-1" />
  </div>
  
  <p>
    Let's start with the basics. These are the <strong>core requirements</strong> 
    your Engineering Portfolio has to meet before you worry about anything else.
  </p>

  <h2>Why Requirements Matter</h2>
  <p>
    Judges go through a ton of portfolios at competition. If yours clearly meets all the 
    requirements, it's way easier for them to score (and easier to score <em>well</em>). Missing 
    something basic can really hurt you, even if your technical work is great.
  </p>

  <h2>Core Requirements</h2>
  <p>These are all outlined in the game manual:</p>

  <div class="req-grid">
    <div class="req-card">
      <span class="req-num">1</span>
      <div>
        <strong>Page Limit</strong>
        <p>No more than 15 pages of content (excluding the cover)</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="req-card">
      <span class="req-num">2</span>
      <div>
        <strong>Cover Page</strong>
        <p>A cover page with your team number (name encouraged)</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="req-card">
      <span class="req-num">3</span>
      <div>
        <strong>Page Size</strong>
        <p>US Letter (8.5" x 11") or A4 (210mm x 297mm). No other sizes.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="req-card">
      <span class="req-num">4</span>
      <div>
        <strong>Table of Contents</strong>
        <p>Makes navigation easy for judges. Highly recommended.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Sample Cover Page Example -->
  <h2>Sample Cover Page</h2>
  <p>Your cover page is the first thing judges see. Here's what a solid cover looks like:</p>

  <div class="cover-example">
    <div class="cover-page">
      <div class="cover-team-num">12345</div>
      <div class="cover-team-name">AVOCADO</div>
      <div class="cover-season">DECODE &bull; 2025-2026</div>
      <div class="cover-hero-img">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="48" height="48" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="2" y="6" width="20" height="12" rx="2"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/><path d="M6 6V4"/><path d="M18 6V4"/><path d="m7 18 3-3"/><path d="m14 15 3 3"/></svg>
        <span>Robot / Team Photo</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cover-mini-toc">
        <div class="cover-toc-title">Contents</div>
        <div class="cover-toc-entries">
          <div class="cover-toc-line"><span>Overview</span><span>1</span></div>
          <div class="cover-toc-line"><span>Design Process</span><span>2</span></div>
          <div class="cover-toc-line"><span>Subsystems</span><span>4</span></div>
          <div class="cover-toc-line"><span>Software</span><span>7</span></div>
          <div class="cover-toc-line"><span>Impact</span><span>9</span></div>
          <div class="cover-toc-line"><span>Results</span><span>11</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-annotations">
      <div class="cover-note">
        <span class="cover-dot"></span>
        Team number &amp; name in BIG, bold text - judges spot it instantly
      </div>
      <div class="cover-note">
        <span class="cover-dot"></span>
        Large robot or team photo - this is the visual centerpiece
      </div>
      <div class="cover-note">
        <span class="cover-dot"></span>
        Small table of contents at the bottom - easy for judges to scan
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="callout tip">
    <strong><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" style="display: inline-block; vertical-align: -0.15em; margin-right: 0.25em;"><path d="M15 14c.2-1 .7-1.7 1.5-2.5 1-.9 1.5-2.2 1.5-3.5A6 6 0 0 0 6 8c0 1 .2 2.2 1.5 3.5.7.7 1.3 1.5 1.5 2.5"></path><path d="M9 18h6"></path><path d="M10 22h4"></path></svg>Pro Tip:</strong> Always check the current season's game manual for the exact requirements. 
    Rules can change year to year!
  </div>

  <h2>Page Structure</h2>
  <p>A typical Engineering Portfolio includes these sections:</p>
  
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Section</th>
        <th>Purpose</th>
        <th>Typical Pages</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Cover Page</td>
        <td>Team identity, branding, table of contents</td>
        <td>1 (not counted in total)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Team Overview</td>
        <td>Intro to your team, roles, mission</td>
        <td>1</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Robot Subsystems Overview</td>
        <td>Describe each component of your robot, what it does, and how it improved this season</td>
        <td>3</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Software/Programming</td>
        <td>Highlight your software architecture, unique algorithms, and programming challenges</td>
        <td>1-2</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Finances and Sustainability</td>
        <td>How your team recruits members, trains/builds skills, and manages finances</td>
        <td>2</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Community Impact</td>
        <td>Describe your team's outreach, events, and STEM promotion efforts</td>
        <td>2</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>That doesn't quite add up to 15, right? That's because you get some flexibility to combine sections or add extra ones based on what your team's story looks like. Just make sure all the required content is there and the overall flow makes sense.</p>

  <h2>Next Steps</h2>
  <p>
    Now that you know the basics, let's move on to best practices for actually 
    putting your portfolio together.
  </p>

  <LessonNav 
    prev={{ title: "How to Use This Tutorial", href: "/lessons/lesson-0/" }}
    next={{ title: "Best Practices", href: "/lessons/lesson-2/" }}
  />
</Layout>

<style>
  .req-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin: 1.25rem 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .req-card {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.85rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.15rem;
    background: var(--bg-surface-solid);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
  }

  .req-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--border-accent);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
  }

  .req-num {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 32px;
    height: 32px;
    background: var(--accent);
    color: #fff;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .req-card strong {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
  }

  .req-card > div p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .req-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .cover-example {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  /* Cover page example */
  .cover-example {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 240px 1fr;
    gap: 2.5rem;
    align-items: start;
    margin: 1.25rem 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .cover-page {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 1.25rem 1rem;
    background: var(--bg-surface-solid);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
    min-height: 340px;
    aspect-ratio: 8.5 / 11;
  }

  .cover-team-num {
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .cover-team-name {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    margin-bottom: 0.1rem;
  }

  .cover-season {
    font-size: 0.55rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  /* Large robot/team image placeholder */
  .cover-hero-img {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 0.35rem;
    width: 90%;
    flex: 1;
    min-height: 120px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    background: var(--accent-faint);
    border: 2px dashed var(--accent-subtle);
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .cover-hero-img span {
    font-size: 0.55rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  /* Small / mini table of contents */
  .cover-mini-toc {
    width: 90%;
    padding: 0.35rem 0.5rem;
    background: var(--bg-surface-hover);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .cover-toc-title {
    font-size: 0.55rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
    text-align: center;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .cover-toc-entries {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .cover-toc-line {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    font-size: 0.48rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    padding: 0.08rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px dotted var(--border);
  }

  .cover-annotations {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    padding-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .cover-note {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .cover-dot {
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--accent);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
</style>


